{"id": "1073", "instruction": "What is the value of $\\sqrt[4] {\\frac{3+2^{4} \\sqrt{5}} {3-2^{4} \\sqrt{5}}}$?\n\nOptions:\nA. $$\n\\frac{\\sqrt[4]{3}+1} {\\sqrt[4]{3}-1}\n$$\nB. $$\n\\frac{\\sqrt[4]{2}+1} {\\sqrt[4]{2}-1}\n$$\nC. $$\n\\frac{2+\\sqrt{5}} {2-\\sqrt{5}}\n$$\nD. $$\n\\frac{\\sqrt[4] {5}+1} {\\sqrt[4] {5}-1}\n$$\nE. $$\n\\frac{3+\\sqrt{5}} {3-\\sqrt{5}}\n$$\nF. $$\n\\frac{\\sqrt{5}+1} {\\sqrt{5}-1}\n$$\nG. $$\n\\frac{\\sqrt[4] {5}-1} {\\sqrt[4] {5}+1}\n$$\nH. $$\n\\frac{4+\\sqrt{5}} {4-\\sqrt{5}}\n$$\nI. $$\n\\frac{\\sqrt[3]{5}+1} {\\sqrt[3]{5}-1}\n$$\nJ. $$\n\\frac{\\sqrt[4] {5}-\\sqrt{5}} {\\sqrt[4] {5}+\\sqrt{5}}\n$$", "output": "D"}
